Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.13,0:01:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Every world has ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.17,0:01:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And every house is haunted by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.84,0:01:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the palace of the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.68,0:01:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially the palace of the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.36,0:01:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With the systems programmers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.86,0:01:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately you've been with them\Nmore than with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.69,0:01:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You've set them a large task.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.99,0:01:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we look to replace them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.66,0:01:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll see it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can count on you, Demerzel?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.62,0:02:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,To see it through?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.13,0:02:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Cleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.21,0:02:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And not just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.55,0:02:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I always assumed\Nyou'd stay on after I was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.01,0:02:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But it occurred to me,\Nin the near-darkness of my life鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.60,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't take anything for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.14,0:02:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm loyal to the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.06,0:02:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but will the Empire be loyal to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't always shown\Nbenevolence to your kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're becoming sentimental,\Nverging on maudlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.53,0:02:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm leaving everything in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.46,0:02:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you unhappy with your successor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.25,0:02:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We can still revisit\Nthe idea of marriage and an heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.50,0:02:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Demerzel, for all you are,\Nand maybe because of it鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.26,0:02:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there are things you will never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.81,0:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I may someday know death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But I doubt you will feel\Nit arrived too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.07,0:03:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have seen\Nthe completion of the Star Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.61,0:03:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Me. My mind. My eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have ridden up\Nto the orbital platform together
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.00,0:03:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and looked down on all that we had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.79,0:03:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.92,0:03:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your continuity is assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-Do you think of him often?\N-You know the way I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't forget anything or anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.31,0:03:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire is always on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.98,0:03:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The platform's orbit\Nis dying at an accelerated rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.86,0:04:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so say the physicists,\Nwho worry it'll just fall on their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.62,0:04:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Their job is to worry over those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.58,0:04:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.42,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it is still yours,\Nbut no longer mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.17,0:04:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is no longer his.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.47,0:04:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How you spend this last day is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of you is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.06,0:04:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow I doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But thank you for trying to make me\Nfeel unique as I shuffle off the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.90,0:04:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hardest on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.20,0:04:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He only had the infant Dawn\Nto place on the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.37,0:04:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A baby with his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.33,0:04:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Identical in every respect,\Nbut a baby nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.17,0:04:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think of him, that's what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.84,0:04:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He also had you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please see Master Ilan, Empire.\NHe's waiting for your final fitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.45,0:05:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.33,0:05:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The details, they're perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For the pick stitching?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.96,0:05:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The jade, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoo, shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.15,0:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry, Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.53,0:05:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lost weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-I am sure your frame is--\N-I am shrinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is beginning to see me\Nfrom a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.08,0:06:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The garment is singular, Ilan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.62,0:06:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be a privilege\Nto wear it at my ascension.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.09,0:06:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-Shall we finish the job?\N-Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ilan, let's let the girl have the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.49,0:06:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dusk? I didn't know you'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.45,0:06:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anacreon. Thespis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:06:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you will speak of them\Nafter I'm gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.00,0:07:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have broken the barbarians.\NCast them adrift.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you have us say\Nthat you haven't said?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I'm still trying to decide\Nwhat to say that I haven't said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.35,0:07:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,About the Outer Reach?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,About anything. About whether any of this\Nis truly within our power to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However many words I have left,\NI would hate to waste them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You waste them\Nwhen you speak of the Outer Reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I speak of Seldon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.94,0:07:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A man long dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.61,0:07:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And soon forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.74,0:07:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean his words\Nhave no more worth in this Empire?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, the Empire is strong--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleon I's legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's a way to save it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.09,0:07:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Stabilize it with propulsive lifts?\NPush it out into the heavens?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To what end?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.30,0:07:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To the end that we not destroy\Nthe last remnants of Cleon I's dream
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.60,0:07:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for lack of our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.52,0:08:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We are the great dream of Cleon I,\Nnot the Star Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The dreamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.84,0:08:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.13,0:08:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.18,0:08:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think I've ever been able\Nto make that face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.04,0:09:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come. Your brothers have your last gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to thank you, Brothers,\Nfor this beautiful meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.55,0:09:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can taste the care\Nyou put into each bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.89,0:09:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your time and your attention\Nis deeply appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.31,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very welcome, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.98,0:09:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is not the gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.73,0:10:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Trantor, the eye of the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.41,0:10:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He was glorious, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.24,0:10:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please respect and enjoy the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.99,0:10:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.87,0:10:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will build something greater\Nin his honor. For you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.54,0:10:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Please respect and enjoy the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.64,0:12:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be here. You know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.51,0:12:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't be the first one\Nwho wanted to see my youngest self.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.10,0:12:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why we made the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.15,0:12:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard that song before.\NOr have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.78,0:12:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder the Empire loves you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.49,0:12:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I find I cannot quite look on that child\Nas an innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.42,0:12:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Seldon wasn't right鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.09,0:12:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there is something unnatural in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.42,0:12:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You should rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange, watching yourself being born.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.10,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep. I'll see you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.64,0:14:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw you tonight鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.19,0:14:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,watching our first brother\Nin the old Star Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.44,0:14:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we not enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.19,0:14:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why you miss him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.61,0:14:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, sweet brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You are enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.59,0:14:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you always leave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have grown into our greatness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dawn, now Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:15:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Dusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.56,0:16:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the new Dawn, just awoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a long, beautiful day ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.74,0:16:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Darkness, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream lives on in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.05,0:16:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you kept it alive in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.70,0:17:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.54,0:17:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.67,0:17:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Demerzel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't forget anything or anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.49,0:17:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire is always on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.41,0:18:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.02,0:19:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To be alive is to know ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We hear their whispers if we listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.08,0:19:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We are haunted by prophets, all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.04,0:19:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you certain you want it erased,\NBrother Dawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.55,0:19:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've outgrown it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.64,0:19:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We ignore the dead at our peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.52,0:19:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Empire cycled through\Na generation of Cleons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the Foundation began colonizing Terminus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.99,0:19:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Empire underestimated Hari.\NWe all did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.03,0:20:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hari had predicted the Cleons would opt\Nfor exile over execution鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.00,0:20:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that his followers' end point\Nwould be Terminus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Every aspect of their arrival\Nwas predetermined鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.77,0:20:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when the colonists would land鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.94,0:20:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,where they would build their outpost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.34,0:20:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So imagine their surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when they discovered that\Nsomething else was already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What in Seldon's name is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't in the surveys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.21,0:21:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we go back?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.79,0:21:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back where, Mari?\NThis was always a one-way journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.67,0:21:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'll check it out.\N-No. We go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.93,0:21:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lowre, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.85,0:21:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah. Yeah.\N-Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm just a little light-headed.\N-Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.07,0:21:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.90,0:22:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Abbas! Get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.50,0:22:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It became known as the Vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.75,0:22:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And over the decades,\Ncountless myths grew up around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.92,0:22:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an ancient artifact left by aliens鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.51,0:22:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a surveillance outpost\Nsent ahead by the Cleons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.39,0:22:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All the settlers knew for certain
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.60,0:22:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,was that the Vault wouldn't allow\Nanyone to approach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.44,0:22:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they kept away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.25,0:22:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The slow ship was scuttled鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.80,0:23:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a refuge built from its bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.55,0:23:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was once mysterious\Nbecame mundane.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.44,0:23:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Her teachers say she's difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.48,0:23:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She's an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.36,0:23:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not listening to me, Abbas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.91,0:23:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a dreamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.16,0:23:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She's distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.04,0:23:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a thinker, like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.17,0:23:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She's aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.88,0:23:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at her. She's fascinated by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.31,0:23:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.89,0:23:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.23,0:23:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think's inside it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:23:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.06,0:23:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do you know it's dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.49,0:24:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.06,0:25:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.94,0:25:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.44,0:26:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One of these days you'll get me,\Nand you'll be so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.15,0:26:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.32,0:26:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, coordinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.82,0:26:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-Which parts?\N-Right boot with left boot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.11,0:26:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How did I miss that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.49,0:26:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How goes the wild work?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.41,0:26:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just got back from\Npatrolling the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.45,0:26:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lichen beds are shrinking.\NIce lunes are already heading south.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.50,0:26:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Means we're gonna have a nice warm spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.46,0:26:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me you don't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.67,0:26:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What, the stench of sulfur?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.71,0:26:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the frostbite?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.80,0:26:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, being a warden suits you\Na lot better than it ever did me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.47,0:26:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. That's a big one, hey?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.60,0:26:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Bishop's claw, female.\NMaybe 600 kilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.31,0:26:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been testing the fence\Nlate at night the last few weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.31,0:26:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna call her Maybel. She's a loner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.40,0:26:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor, why have you got me out here\Nat this time in the morning, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.62,0:26:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know when my daughter's procrastinating.\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.87,0:27:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a little test.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.83,0:27:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's wrong with the null field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.17,0:27:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And what made you check it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.05,0:27:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. A feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.92,0:27:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked it out. I got evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.84,0:27:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. And have you told her yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.80,0:27:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanted you to know first.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.22,0:27:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate that.\NBut it is for her to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.43,0:27:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And stress the evidence part.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.09,0:27:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the efforts of Dr. Seldon,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.51,0:28:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleon XII established our refuge鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.26,0:28:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In terms of timekeeping, the water clock\Nis the more precise instrument.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.89,0:28:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. But it also requires water\Nto work, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.52,0:28:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.90,0:28:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens when the water runs out,\NNovice Jord?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.23,0:28:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For a sundial, all you need is the gnomon.\NThat's the blade sticking out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.20,0:28:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course鈥� the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.32,0:28:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hari Seldon entrusted us with rebuilding\Ncivilization after the collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.54,0:28:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't assume anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether or not our future survivors\Nwill be able to read,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.33,0:28:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,or what language they'll speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.71,0:28:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even know\Nwhat worlds they'll be scattered upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.59,0:28:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they find themselves\Non Cygnus Prime,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.01,0:28:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where the only moisture to be gained\Nis from weeping vines?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.31,0:28:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, this water clock is more precise,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.19,0:28:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but the sundial is more practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.94,0:28:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't provide for every condition\Nor contingency our descendants will face.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.77,0:28:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,By the same token,\Nwe can't preserve every innovation,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.32,0:28:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have to choose and keep choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.36,0:28:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the fall comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.49,0:29:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have picked the water clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.41,0:29:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could have,\Nif you were still training here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.16,0:29:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, that was--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.75,0:29:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're suited to where you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.37,0:29:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping us safe,\Nmaking sure the Foundation survives--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.54,0:29:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm making sure you survive.\NThe Foundation--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.42,0:29:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing.\NWe are the Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.42,0:29:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not.\NBut you believe. And that is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.63,0:29:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Do not make this sound like a cult.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.55,0:29:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us in our generation know\Nwhat real religious fervor looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.89,0:29:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you even wanna know\Nwhat I came to tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.48,0:29:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I don't like being near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.52,0:29:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said you'd want evidence, and this\Nyou gotta experience for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.70,0:29:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The null field is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.45,0:29:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The field used to start there.\NNow it starts here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.45,0:29:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If it keeps expanding,\Nwe might need to clear out the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.82,0:30:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the first time\NI found you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.74,0:30:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Four years old, middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.70,0:30:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,standing right under it\Nlike it was鈥� nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.58,0:30:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you wouldn't turn\Nwhen I called your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.25,0:30:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I thought it was calling to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.37,0:30:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.29,0:30:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an imaginary friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.30,0:30:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I lay on the ground and tried to crawl\Nto you, but the pain was too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.55,0:30:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You just鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.97,0:30:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.85,0:30:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't understand\Nwhy the Vault was hurting you but not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.35,0:30:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're special, Salvor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.90,0:30:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You always have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.61,0:30:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why keep it a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.07,0:31:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father and I didn't want\Npeople treating you differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.49,0:31:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but they do, Mom. They always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.08,0:31:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.12,0:31:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the Vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.46,0:31:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it calling to you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.51,0:31:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in words.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.88,0:31:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Make your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.05,0:31:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's waking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.18,0:31:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You and the other encyclopedists,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.77,0:31:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you've been preparing for\Nsome distant crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.56,0:31:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.02,0:31:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.53,0:31:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Gia! Keir! Guys, Hugo's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.74,0:31:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hugo's here!\N-Hugo's here! Hugo's here, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.58,0:31:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hugo's here!\N-Come on, Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.83,0:31:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hugo!\N-Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.62,0:31:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.67,0:31:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. Look at that! Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.09,0:32:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-Cut through this way!\N-Whoa. Hey, now. Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.10,0:32:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, you can't get me.\N-Through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.06,0:32:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. Come on.\NHurry up! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.23,0:32:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Poly, come on! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.90,0:32:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hugo! Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.86,0:32:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hugo!\N-Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.90,0:32:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Four-sworn, Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.20,0:32:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, ladies.\NWhat can I do for you grown adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.58,0:32:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Got anything for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.91,0:32:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Korellian chocolate. Knock yourselves out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.91,0:32:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want chocolate.\NHow about some beer?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.71,0:32:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you come back and see me\Nwhen you got hair on your chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.84,0:32:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't come begging for it\Nlike wayward puppies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.71,0:32:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not begging. We're鈥� trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.05,0:32:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? What for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.05,0:32:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How about our sparkling wit and company?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.47,0:32:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.02,0:32:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell you what.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.19,0:32:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you clowns could help me load out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.27,0:33:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I might be able to scrounge up something\Na little more age-appropriate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.23,0:33:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal. I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.03,0:33:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We all will.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.19,0:33:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.28,0:33:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come on, guys.\N-Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.78,0:33:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-Keir, catch. Poly.\N-I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.46,0:33:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That smells terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.13,0:33:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It should. It's sealant for my gum boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.88,0:33:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,More onions than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.13,0:33:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have used the wrong recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.93,0:33:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a tragic mishap.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.73,0:33:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.60,0:33:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a man in my kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.15,0:33:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.15,0:33:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-nine long hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And how's the rest of the galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.16,0:33:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's big.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.87,0:33:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You should see it sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.41,0:33:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.05,0:34:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Irina Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.39,0:34:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one continent,\Nbut it's tropical all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.59,0:34:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got bugs the size of dogs\Nand just as cuddly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.10,0:34:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Dropped off medicine, I picked up fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.27,0:34:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Such is the itinerant life\Nof the wayward purveyor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.23,0:34:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-Where'd you take the fruit?\N-To Hesperus.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.77,0:34:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Which you could describe\Nas well as me by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.32,0:34:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was off on a whirlwind tour\Nof this little cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.45,0:34:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Once they started trading,\Nthey couldn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.62,0:34:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Little rectangular situation\Nof workers and sugar, rum, cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.12,0:34:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you've got a handful of moons,\Nyou should see what they got.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.38,0:34:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky looks like spilled coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.54,0:34:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-Spilled coins?\N-Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.38,0:34:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.92,0:34:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you need to go.\NGet off this ball of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.18,0:34:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-I've got responsibilities here.\N-Oh, but you didn't pick them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.30,0:34:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, they're still mine. And鈥�
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.93,0:35:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to know you've got reasons\Nand not know what they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.52,0:35:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Reasons you're important to this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.40,0:35:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible.\NA little egotistical, but possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.73,0:35:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say I was important.\NI said I can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.11,0:35:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of leaving,\Nwould you like dinner now or after?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.24,0:35:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,After sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.39,0:36:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.60,0:36:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.97,0:36:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a weird feeling.\NI'm gonna walk the perimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.98,0:36:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What, because that's\Nwhere the weird feeling is coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.77,0:36:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that is in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.40,0:36:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.78,0:36:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I said,\N"Let me get my pants," you'd say?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.36,0:36:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No pants for the next 25 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.58,0:36:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,-Will you be mad later?\N-Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.39,0:37:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.81,0:37:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.07,0:37:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop. It's after curfew.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.30,0:37:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.34,0:38:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.51,0:39:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.43,0:39:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard a shot. What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.02,0:39:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I crazy, or is that ship Anacreon?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.82,0:39:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.57,0:39:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But not about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.87,0:39:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there are three.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.08,0:39:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hail them.\N-We already have. No answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.50,0:39:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're ignoring our approach vectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.63,0:39:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we send one of our shuttles\Nto meet them?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.59,0:39:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your unarmed shuttles?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.96,0:39:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are corvettes. Gunships.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.43,0:39:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is he here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.80,0:39:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he knows what gunships look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.89,0:39:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, he's Thespin.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.31,0:39:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Been off-world since the bombings.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.35,0:39:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible. That would make you--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.93,0:39:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Pushing 70. But I spent half that\Ncryosleeping between ports.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.81,0:39:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When you tow freight to Anacreon,\Nit pays to be blood-neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:40:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-Anacreon is under imperial sanction.\N-Grow up, Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.74,0:40:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a mistake.\NMaybe they wandered off course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.78,0:40:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're literally trying to sneak in\Nunder our radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.78,0:40:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We are a scientific outpost.\NWe have nothing of value here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.95,0:40:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayor, have the Anacreons\Never made landfall here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.58,0:40:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No Anacreons, no Thespins.\NNo one in 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.50,0:40:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Under imperial edict,\NTerminus is off-limit to all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.38,0:40:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be connected to the Vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.05,0:40:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.26,0:40:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The null field's expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.13,0:40:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,-I noticed it yesterday.\N-How fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.55,0:40:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, the Anacreons showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.39,0:40:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Technically, we are an imperial outpost.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.01,0:40:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lord knows the Anacreons have\Na bone to pick with the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.48,0:40:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting\Nthe Vault might be an Anacreon--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.69,0:40:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm suggesting the Vault knew something\Nand reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.11,0:40:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it even warned us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.44,0:40:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the Vault was signaling you\Nbecause you're somehow, what, special?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.24,0:40:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor is an outlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.45,0:40:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to think whether the Plan\Ncould have possibly predicted--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.16,0:40:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget the Plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.54,0:40:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Seldon's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.75,0:40:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When are any of you\Ngonna start thinking for yourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.79,0:40:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's enough.\NWe don't need to make this complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.08,0:41:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Anacreons have ignored our hails,\Nand they are violating imperial aerospace.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.51,0:41:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our course of action is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.51,0:41:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll uplink to the communications buoy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.38,0:41:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as we hit\Nthe next rotational window.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.18,0:41:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll call the Empire, and they will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.31,0:41:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.85,0:41:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To check out the armory.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.85,0:41:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Anacreons come knocking\Nbefore the Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.32,0:41:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to know what kind of violence\Nwe can muster.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.03,0:41:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the last time\Nthese were broken down?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.86,0:41:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-So we're a little complacent.\N-I've got an ion pistol, if that helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.62,0:41:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, anything we could use\Nin the curation stores?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.62,0:41:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A few hand axes,\Na shepherd's sling from Weaver's World.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.29,0:41:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-I should've been on top of this.\N-Not your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.54,0:41:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-No? I keep you safe, remember?\N-Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.25,0:41:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally I propose alcohol\Nat a juncture like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.71,0:41:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Rotational window's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.17,0:41:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Handshake protocol.\NIt just takes a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.65,0:42:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.90,0:42:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Comms buoy's not responding\Nto any of our pings. It's gone dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.90,0:42:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Use another one then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.19,0:42:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.36,0:42:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't contact the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.12,0:42:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep trying. Don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.62,0:42:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be something as simple as\Na meteor shower. It'll clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.75,0:42:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,On the heels of an Anacreon flyby?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming the Anacreons\Nintend landfall here,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.09,0:42:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,how long before they arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.59,0:42:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on their current approach,\NI'd say another 40 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.48,0:42:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.43,0:43:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.56,0:43:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.52,0:43:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychohistory.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.94,0:43:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All of Hari's work\Nexpressed as a mathematical equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.44,0:43:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I took it from his office\Nthe night after his funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.99,0:43:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,His numbers are the basis\Nfor why we do what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.78,0:43:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,On the ship, there were two people\Nwho could actually understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.99,0:43:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hari Seldon and Gaal Dornick.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.25,0:43:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you make anything of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.71,0:43:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? No, not likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.05,0:43:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor, if you were part of the Plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.34,0:43:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it would make it a lot easier\Nfor me to believe in all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.55,0:44:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, big surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.55,0:44:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was worth a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.68,0:44:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.59,0:44:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you,\Ndifferent's not the same as special.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.16,0:45:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Comms buoy is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.33,0:45:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an ominous happenstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.66,0:45:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You should probably hightail it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.46,0:45:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.21,0:45:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Anacreons will be here in two days.\NMaybe less.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.42,0:45:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You would be safer anywhere but here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.55,0:45:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The scenery is so beautiful\Nthis time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.35,0:45:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Vast wastelands of frozen lune shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.77,0:45:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm serious, Hugo.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.06,0:45:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.48,0:45:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.73,0:45:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't your fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.15,0:45:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah? Whose fight is it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.32,0:45:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Seldon's?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.37,0:45:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's not your fight either.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.75,0:45:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Come away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.17,0:45:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.25,0:45:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.21,0:45:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I have to protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.55,0:46:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To be alive is to know ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.85,0:46:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Empire feared Hari\Nbecause he could forecast the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.77,0:46:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But, in reality, all he was doing\Nwas reexamining the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.48,0:46:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.65,0:46:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention to the patterns\Nand we can presage what comes next.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.33,0:46:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To be alive is to know ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.50,0:46:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We hear their whispers if we listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.77,0:46:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.81,0:47:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.02,0:47:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What got you, Maybel?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.40,0:47:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is gonna hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.21,0:47:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.00,0:48:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop your weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.89,0:48:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.01,0:48:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvor Hardin, warden of Terminus.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.77,0:48:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anacreons aren't allowed on imperial soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.20,0:48:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.24,0:48:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The ghosts of the dead haunt\Nthe skeletons that were once our homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.70,0:48:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.37,0:48:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're hungry for what's ours.